article.headline: Jordan Johnson scores career-high 40 as New Orleans beats Texas A&M-CC 83-80
article.description: — Jordan Johnson scored a career-high 40 points and New Orleans took down Texas A&M-CC 83-80 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Jordan Johnson scores career-high 40 as New Orleans beats Texas A&M-CC 83-80
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- — Jordan Johnson scored a career-high 40 points and New Orleans took down Texas A&M-CC 83-80 on Saturday night. Johnson, who scored 36 points last time out, topped is previous career-high of 39 points, set last season. Mason Jones scored 11 points, as did James Glisson III for the Privateers (7-9, 2-1 Southland Conference). Dian Wright-Forde finished with 23 points for the Islanders (9-7, 2-1). Lance Amir-Paul added 16 points and six rebounds for Texas A&M-CC. Jordan Roberts also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
